  "plainContent": {
    "en": "Use this checklist when you are setting up Oviond for the first time.\n\n*   Create or join your agency account.\n    \n*   Add your first client.\n    \n*   Connect at least one data source for that client.\n    \n*   Create a report or dashboard.\n    \n*   Add widgets that use the connected data source.\n    \n*   Share the report with your client or test an automation.\n    \n\nIf you get stuck, start by checking whether the client has a connected data source and whether the widget date range contains data.\n\nScreenshots\n-----------\n\nUse this screenshot to find the Clients area and start the setup flow.\n\nScreenshot guide\n----------------\n\nUse the screenshot below as a quick map for the first setup step.\n\nReal Oviond Clients screen with numbered markers\n\nWhat the numbers show\n---------------------\n\n1.  1\\. Use the left sidebar to open Clients, Templates, Automations, or Settings.\n    \n2.  2\\. Click Add Client to start creating a new client workspace.\n    \n3.  3\\. Use the client card to open an existing client and check its website and data-source count."
  },
